OL,3,CHeathrow accuses Government of
OL,4,C'curtailing UK's global connectivity'
OL,6,FHeathrow Airport has accused the
OL,7,FGovernment of "curtailing the UK's
OL,8,Fglobal connectivity".
OL,10,FThe west London airport criticised
OL,11,Fmeasures such as introducing a #10 fee
OL,12,Ffor some transiting passengers and the
OL,13,Frefusal to resume tax-free shopping
OL,14,Ffor international visitors.
OL,16,FThe Government launched the electronic
OL,17,Ftravel authorisation (ETA) scheme in
OL,18,FNovember 2023 for people entering or
OL,19,Ftransiting through the UK without
OL,20,Flegal residence or a visa.
